I'll modify the code to clear the array before populating it. The `memset()` call will zero out the entire `mappedQoS_FlowsToAdd` array, preventing any stale configurations from persisting. This ensures a clean slate for each new QoS flow mapping.

The loop iterates through the QoS flows, assigning QFI values and determining the DRB status based on the 5QI value. By clearing the array first, I prevent any potential conflicts or incorrect mappings from previous configurations.

